 unwritten, even though, since the 1960s, numerous interactions and aesthetic negotiations have taken place in literature, film, and in societal debates and theories that have driven the transformation of the political system. This volume opens up an unexpected perspective on informal relations and potentials that have so far received little attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aEinwanderungsgesellschaft. 4aErzähltechnik. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLiteraturgeschichte. 4aMigration. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aNarratives of Migration: A Different History of German Culture.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831107313850 cprintz978311073658840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110731347zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110731347zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110731347/original  a978-3-11-075070-6 DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DKUb2021  aZDB-23-GOA